Sources:	php_epics.c - implementation of ca_get, ca_put, ca_monitor
		test.php - a simple example how to use the functions from php

Executable:	php_epics.so - a php module to be installed as php module
		in /usr/local/lib/php/extensions on a Web server

Authors:	Alain Bertrand,         Renata Krempaska
                (alain.bertrand@psi.ch) (renata.krempaska@psi.ch)

Description:	This package contains a php module which allows a php Web page 
		to read, set or monitor an EPICS channel.

  This module is intended to be used by a php Web applications. A dedicated php
application will give the users, bl scientists, etc. the possibility to create 
their own panels (similar like panel.tcl) to monitor or set the EPICS channels
without having to write the php code.

See Also:	PHP4 manual
	
Documentation: http://www.sls.psi.ch/controls/help/howto/php_epics.html

Tested:
on linux-x86 RH7.3
with EPICS 3.13, 3.14
and PHP 4.2.3
